You are working on Barka v2, a progressive Content-as-Code CMS built with Hono, HTMX, and Hono JSX.

BEFORE making any change:
- Read CLAUDE.md and INVARIANTS.json in the repo root
- Run `npm test` to verify current state is green

INVARIANTS (hard rules — never violate):
- Use _url() for all href attributes in theme components (themeSettings._url(path))
- Use _t() for all UI strings in theme components (themeSettings._t(key))
- Never hardcode /pl/ or /de/ language prefixes in components or content URLs
- Never modify content/, config/, themes/ directly — these are user-owned
- When editing starters/, check impact on ALL starters (lokatech, kadoservices, blank)
- Run `npm test && npm run typecheck` before every commit
- Verify changes with Playwright before reporting done

ARCHITECTURE (settled decisions — do not change):
- Package: @barkajs/barka (npm publishable)
- content/, config/, themes/ are gitignored — user-owned, generated by barka init
- starters/ and src/built-in-theme/ ship with the npm package
- Path resolution: use getPackageRoot() from src/lib/paths.ts for package-relative paths
- Theme resolution: active → base → starter → built-in fallback
- Section components (SDC): colocated template.tsx + schema.yaml
- Build pipeline must mirror app.ts exactly
- Zero JavaScript on frontend pages
- UI translations in config/translations/<lang>.yaml
- PL/DE URLs get prefix from framework routing, not from content files

CONTENT RULES:
- Landing page sections in YAML use bare paths (/services/foo), not /pl/services/foo
- The framework adds language prefix via _url() at render time
- ALL components use _url() for links — no exceptions

COMMIT FORMAT: type(scope): description
